Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Curteis was born about 1304, in Hanbury, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in Niton, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1304–":"umbes 1304–Surnud","1330–1391":"1330–1391","1304–Male":"1304–Surnud","1304":"1304","Abt 1304":"umbes 1304","1330":"1330","1391":"1391","Hanbury, Staffordshire, England":"Hanbury, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Niton, Hampshire, England":"Niton, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1304–":"noin 1304–Kuollut","1330–1391":"1330–1391","1304–Male":"1304–Kuollut","1304":"1304","Abt 1304":"noin 1304","1330":"1330","1391":"1391","Hanbury, Staffordshire, England":"Hanbury, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Niton, Hampshire, England":"Niton, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1304–":"environ 1304–Décédé","1330–1391":"1330–1391","1304–Male":"1304–Décédé","1304":"1304","Abt 1304":"environ 1304","1330":"1330","1391":"1391","Hanbury, Staffordshire, England":"Hanbury, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Niton, Hampshire, England":"Niton, Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Curteis est né environ 1304, à Hanbury, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé à N